description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced, enthusiastic and motivated dietitian to join the community based adult eating disorders team in Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for providing specialist dietetic input within our adult eating disorders team (0.8wte) as well as 1 day per week (0.2 wte) within the organisation’s inpatient mental health dietetics team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working closely with the multi-disciplinary eating disorder team, under the supervision of the lead eating disorders dietitian.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also have the opportunity to contribute towards service development and help shape the delivery of nutritional care within a mental health setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be based at the Eating Disorders Service base in Belper, but includes county wide clinics and inpatient liaison so a vehicle and ability to travel across the county to various locations is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The inpatient mental health dietetics team are based at the Kingsway Hospital in Derby.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to pandemic restrictions, we are currently able to offer some remote working on a temporary basis on certain working days. This may vary based on need for supervision, training and inpatient coverage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be clinically supported by a friendly, experienced multi-disciplinary eating disorders team as well as a small Trust-wide dietetic team who are committed to continued professional development and training opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a placement provider for student dietitians and are currently involved in A,B and C placements with the University of Nottingham. The post holder will be actively involved in student training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you can demonstrate the willingness to learn and undertake a new challenge we look forward to hearing from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from band 5 dietitians with 2+ years of experience, looking to specialise or gain some experience in a growing and forward thinking area of dietetic practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you wish to discuss this exciting opportunity further, or arrange an informal visit, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Megan Lomax, Lead Eating disorders Dietitian, 07747 006887&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr. Joanna Miatt, Eating Disorders Service Manager, 01773 881467&lt;/p&gt;
